verbose_text: Interleukin-10 (IL-10) is a Th2 anti-inflammatory factor that can inhibit the release of inflammatory factor or anti-TB immunity, in addition to its critical roles in regulating differentiation and function of osteoblasts / osteoclasts [XREF_BIBR, XREF_BIBR].
